121 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLISensorStart (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
122 {
123  bool doReconfig = true;
124  int32_t retVal = 0;
125 
126  /* Only following command syntax will be supported
127  sensorStart
128  sensorStart 0
129  */
130  if (argc == 2)
131  {
132  doReconfig = (bool) atoi (argv[1]);
133 
134  if (doReconfig == true)
135  {
136  CLI_write ("Error: Reconfig is not supported, only argument of 0 is\n"
137  "(do not reconfig, just re-start the sensor) valid\n");
138  return -1;
139  }
140  }
141  else
142  {
143  /* In case there is no argument for sensorStart, always do reconfig */
144  doReconfig = true;
145  }
146 
147  /***********************************************************************************
148  * Do sensor state management to influence the sensor actions
149  ***********************************************************************************/
150 
151  /* Error checking initial state: no partial config is allowed
152  until the first sucessful sensor start state */
153  if ((gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_INIT) ||
154  (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_OPENED))
155  {
156  MMWave_CtrlCfg ctrlCfg;
157 
158  /* need to get number of sub-frames so that next function to check
159  * pending state can work */
160  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionConfig (&ctrlCfg);
161  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames =
162  MmwDemo_RFParser_getNumSubFrames(&ctrlCfg);
163 
164  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState() == 0)
165  {
166  CLI_write ("Error: Full configuration must be provided before sensor can be started "
167  "the first time\n");
168 
169  /* Although not strictly needed, bring back to the initial value since we
170  * are rejecting this first time configuration, prevents misleading debug. */
171  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames = 0;
172 
173  return -1;
174  }
175  }
176 
177  if (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_STARTED)
178  {
179  CLI_write ("Ignored: Sensor is already started\n");
180  return 0;
181  }
182 
183  if (doReconfig == false)
184  {
185  /* User intends to issue sensor start without config, check if no
186  config was issued after stop and generate error if this is the case. */
187  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInNonPendingState() == 0)
188  {
189  /* Message user differently if all config was issued or partial config was
190  issued. */
191  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState())
192  {
193  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided complete new configuration, "
194  "issue \"sensorStart\" (without argument) if you want it to "
195  "take effect\n");
196  }
197  else
198  {
199  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided partial configuration between stop and this "
200  "command and partial configuration cannot be undone."
201  "Issue the full configuration and do \"sensorStart\" \n");
202  }
203  return -1;
204  }
205  }
206  else
207  {
208  /* User intends to issue sensor start with full config, check if all config
209  was issued after stop and generate error if is the case. */
210  MMWave_CtrlCfg ctrlCfg;
211 
212  /* need to get number of sub-frames so that next function to check
213  * pending state can work */
214  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionConfig (&ctrlCfg);
215  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames =
216  MmwDemo_RFParser_getNumSubFrames(&ctrlCfg);
217 
218  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState() == 0)
219  {
220  /* Message user differently if no config was issued or partial config was
221  issued. */
222  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInNonPendingState())
223  {
224  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided no configuration, "
225  "issue \"sensorStart 0\" OR provide "
226  "full configuration and issue \"sensorStart\"\n");
227  }
228  else
229  {
230  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided partial configuration between stop and this "
231  "command and partial configuration cannot be undone."
232  "Issue the full configuration and do \"sensorStart\" \n");
233  }
234  /* Although not strictly needed, bring back to the initial value since we
235  * are rejecting this first time configuration, prevents misleading debug. */
236  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames = 0;
237  return -1;
238  }
239  }
240 
241  /***********************************************************************************
242  * Retreive and check mmwave Open related config before calling openSensor
243  ***********************************************************************************/
244 
245  /* Fill demo's MCB mmWave openCfg structure from the CLI configs*/
246  if (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_INIT)
247  {
248  /* Get the open configuration: */
249  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionOpenConfig (&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg);
250  /* call sensor open */
251  retVal = MmwDemo_openSensor(true);
252  if(retVal != 0)
253  {
254  return -1;
255  }
256  gMmwMssMCB.sensorState = MmwDemo_SensorState_OPENED;
257  }
258  else
259  {
260  /* openCfg related configurations like chCfg, lowPowerMode, adcCfg
261  * are only used on the first sensor start. If they are different
262  * on a subsequent sensor start, then generate a fatal error
263  * so the user does not think that the new (changed) configuration
264  * takes effect, the board needs to be reboot for the new
265  * configuration to be applied.
266  */
267  MMWave_OpenCfg openCfg;
268  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionOpenConfig (&openCfg);
269  /* Compare openCfg->chCfg*/
270  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.chCfg, (void *)&openCfg.chCfg,
271  sizeof(rlChanCfg_t)) != 0)
272  {
273  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
274  }
275 
276  /* Compare openCfg->lowPowerMode*/
277  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.lowPowerMode, (void *)&openCfg.lowPowerMode,
278  sizeof(rlLowPowerModeCfg_t)) != 0)
279  {
280  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
281  }
282  /* Compare openCfg->adcOutCfg*/
283  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.adcOutCfg, (void *)&openCfg.adcOutCfg,
284  sizeof(rlAdcOutCfg_t)) != 0)
285  {
286  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
287  }
288  }
289 
290 
291 
292  /***********************************************************************************
293  * Retrieve mmwave Control related config before calling startSensor
294  ***********************************************************************************/
295  /* Get the mmWave ctrlCfg from the CLI mmWave Extension */
296  if(doReconfig)
297  {
298  /* if MmwDemo_openSensor has non-first time related processing, call here again*/
299  /* call sensor config */
300  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionConfig (&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.ctrlCfg);
301  retVal = MmwDemo_configSensor();
302  if(retVal != 0)
303  {
304  return -1;
305  }
306  }
307  retVal = MmwDemo_startSensor();
308  if(retVal != 0)
309  {
310  return -1;
311  }
312 
313  /***********************************************************************************
314  * Set the state
315  ***********************************************************************************/
316  gMmwMssMCB.sensorState = MmwDemo_SensorState_STARTED;
317  return 0;
318 }

336 {
337  if ((gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_STOPPED) ||

340  {
341  CLI_write ("Ignored: Sensor is already stopped\n");
342  return 0;

345  MmwDemo_stopSensor();
346

348

350  return 0;
351 }

368 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe (int32_t argc, char* argv[], int32_t expectedArgc,
369  int8_t* subFrameNum)
370 {
371  int8_t subframe;
372 
373  /* Sanity Check: Minimum argument check */
374  if (argc != expectedArgc)
375  {
376  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid usage of the CLI command\n");
377  return -1;
378  }
379 
380  /*Subframe info is always in position 1*/
381  subframe = (int8_t) atoi(argv[1]);
382 
383  if(subframe >= (int8_t)RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES)
384  {
385  CLI_write ("Error: Subframe number is invalid\n");
386  return -1;
387  }
388 
389  *subFrameNum = (int8_t)subframe;
390 
391  return 0;
392 }

453 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLICfarCfg (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
454 {
455  DPU_CFARCAProc_CfarCfg cfarCfg;
456  uint32_t procDirection;
457  int8_t subFrameNum;
458  float threshold;
459 
460  if(MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe(argc, argv, 10, &subFrameNum) < 0)
461  {
462  return -1;
463  }
464 
465  /* Initialize configuration: */
466  memset ((void *)&cfarCfg, 0, sizeof(cfarCfg));
467 
468  /* Populate configuration: */
469  procDirection = (uint32_t) atoi (argv[2]);
470  cfarCfg.averageMode = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[3]);
471  cfarCfg.winLen = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[4]);
472  cfarCfg.guardLen = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[5]);
473  cfarCfg.noiseDivShift = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[6]);
474  cfarCfg.cyclicMode = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[7]);
475  threshold = (float) atof (argv[8]);
476  cfarCfg.peakGroupingEn = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[9]);
477 
478  if (threshold > 100.0)
479  {
480  CLI_write("Error: Maximum value for CFAR thresholdScale is 100.0 dB.\n");
481  return -1;
482  }
483 
484  /* threshold is a float value from 0-100dB. It needs to
485  be later converted to linear scale (conversion can only be done
486  when the number of virtual antennas is known) before passing it
487  to CFAR DPU.
488  For now, the threshold will be coded in a 16bit integer in the following
489  way:
490  suppose threshold is a float represented as XYZ.ABC
491  it will be saved as a 16bit integer XYZAB
492  that is, 2 decimal cases are saved.*/
493  threshold = threshold * MMWDEMO_CFAR_THRESHOLD_ENCODING_FACTOR;
494  cfarCfg.thresholdScale = (uint16_t) threshold;
495 
496  /* Save Configuration to use later */
497  if (procDirection == 0)
498  {
499  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfarCfg, MMWDEMO_CFARCFGRANGE_OFFSET,
500  sizeof(cfarCfg), subFrameNum);
501  }
502  else
503  {
504  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfarCfg, MMWDEMO_CFARCFGDOPPLER_OFFSET,
505  sizeof(cfarCfg), subFrameNum);
506  }
507  return 0;
508 }

689 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLICalibDcRangeSig (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
690 {
691  DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg cfg;
692  uint32_t log2NumAvgChirps;
693  int8_t subFrameNum;
694 
695  if(MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe(argc, argv, 6, &subFrameNum) < 0)
696  {
697  return -1;
698  }
699 
700  /* Initialize configuration for DC range signature calibration */
701  memset ((void *)&cfg, 0, sizeof(cfg));
702 
703  /* Populate configuration: */
704  cfg.enabled = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[2]);
705  cfg.negativeBinIdx = (int16_t) atoi (argv[3]);
706  cfg.positiveBinIdx = (int16_t) atoi (argv[4]);
707  cfg.numAvgChirps = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[5]);
708 
709  if (cfg.negativeBinIdx > 0)
710  {
711  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid negative bin index\n");
712  return -1;
713  }
714  if ((cfg.positiveBinIdx - cfg.negativeBinIdx + 1) > DPU_RANGEPROC_SIGNATURE_COMP_MAX_BIN_SIZE)
715  {
716  CLI_write ("Error: Number of bins exceeds the limit\n");
717  return -1;
718  }
719  log2NumAvgChirps = (uint32_t) mathUtils_ceilLog2(cfg.numAvgChirps);
720  if (cfg.numAvgChirps != (1U << log2NumAvgChirps))
721  {
722  CLI_write ("Error: Number of averaged chirps is not power of two\n");
723  return -1;
724  }
725 
726  /* Save Configuration to use later */
727  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfg, MMWDEMO_CALIBDCRANGESIG_OFFSET,
728  sizeof(cfg), subFrameNum);
729 
730  return 0;
731 }
